==English==

===Etymology===
From Greek [[αιματοίδρουν]] (''haimatohidroun'') to sweat blood: ''haimato-'', "blood" + ''hidroun'', "to sweat".

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˌhe-mat-id'ro-sis/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|haematidroses}}

*1. {{symptom}} A very rare disorder in which the patient sweats blood and/or blood pigments, usually resulting from extreme physical and/or mental stress. Also spelled '''hematidrosis''', '''hematohidrosis''' and '''haematohidrosis'''. 

*2. Bloody sweat; sweating blood

